Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.42,0:00:24.14,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.21,0:00:28.08,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Tanabe! Can you see me?!\NIf you can see me, answer me!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.02,0:00:33.27,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Please respond! Somebody!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.97,0:00:35.66,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Is anybody\nout there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.17,0:00:41.10,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Anybody! Come in!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.91,0:00:44.30,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm here! I'm right over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.65,0:00:46.69,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Please, find me!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.64,0:00:53.76,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,2000)}Somebody!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.80,0:02:31.35,F.O. (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\move(523,360,350,355)\fad(760,830)\bord0.1\shad2\fs30\fscx100\fscy100\t(0,5544,\fscx110\fscy100)}Ignition
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.83,0:02:37.31,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Fee, it was an accident.\NDon't blame yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.06,0:02:40.68,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The sun is at the peak of its\N11-year cycle this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.42,0:02:42.75,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, radio reception\nwas bad to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.78,0:02:46.15,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No one could have predicted\nthat solar flare.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.85,0:02:47.90,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And they couldn't have done anything\nabout it even if they had.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.91,0:02:52.87,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,As ship's captain, I'm responsible for\nlosing track of my crew during EVA.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.36,0:02:56.83,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I should've anticipated a comm blackout based on...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.83,0:02:58.54,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...the plasma flow information\nin the space weather report.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.10,0:03:03.18,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I should've called off both\ntheir jobs, not just Tanabe...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.15,0:03:06.71,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He wasn't exposed\nfor all that long.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.34,0:03:09.06,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He might not have been exposed\nto lethal amounts of radiation.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.74,0:03:13.39,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How is he?!\NIs he going to be all right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.05,0:03:16.35,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They said that nothing's\nwrong with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.66,0:03:21.06,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The doctor was shocked, too!\NI didn't catch much radiation at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.72,0:03:26.38,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like I was floating between the Van Allen\nbelts when the radiation was at its peak.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.83,0:03:29.44,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, we were in\nthe Earth's shadow.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.26,0:03:33.92,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He said that most people would've had their nervous systems fried by high-speed particles!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.29,0:03:36.17,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They complimented me\non my dumb luck!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.32,0:03:40.63,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You've got some nerve\nto be laughing!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.40,0:03:45.66,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This whole mess happened because you missed your rendezvous with the target debris...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.04,0:03:47.56,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...and went chasing after it\nlike an idiot, right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.92,0:03:50.51,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And you let go\nof your lifeline, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.51,0:03:52.12,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yesh, ma'ab! I'b zorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.32,0:03:54.06,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You ignore my orders\nlike that again,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.39,0:03:56.19,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...and I'm gonna leave you out there\nto join the debris, got it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.69,0:03:57.38,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,For one thing, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.79,0:03:59.52,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Thank goodness...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.42,0:04:01.30,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so relieved...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.53,0:04:06.24,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you were\ngoing to die...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.26,0:04:10.07,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, sorry for making\nyou worry like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.09,0:04:17.78,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If that's the case, there will be a\nvice president's position opening up.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.05,0:04:21.10,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The top candidate is probably\nyou-know-who.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.85,0:04:25.46,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We certainly can't complain about\nthe Second Division's record.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.75,0:04:28.05,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So, we're finally looking at Vice President Dolf," eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.39,0:04:33.16,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You must be joking! Second Division owes its\nrecord to the fact that he ignores the rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.46,0:04:37.50,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Well, he's certainly expanded our business\nby breaking with tradition.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.90,0:04:43.15,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'll give him that. Still, we can't build good\nrelations with INTO, not with his methods.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.65,0:04:44.20,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.05,0:04:49.07,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'll talk to the company president personally.\NYour people won't have any objections, I take it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.72,0:04:52.43,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Banks are always on the side\nof harmony and order.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.63,0:04:59.41,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Y'know, this goes beyond luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.68,0:05:00.22,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.46,0:05:04.54,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Space loves me! I'm a man who won't die\nbefore he completes his life's ambition!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.86,0:05:05.45,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.81,0:05:07.76,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Go on, ask me!\NAsk me what my life's ambition is.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.02,0:05:10.53,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,To own a spaceship, right?\NYou've told us that a million times.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.86,0:05:14.18,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Look here, you... When a man's talking about\nhis dreams, you just sit back and listen quietly.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.71,0:05:14.38,Alternative (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hoshino-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.78,0:05:15.97,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hoshino Hachirota-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.83,0:05:19.27,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's me.\NAre my discharge papers ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.64,0:05:22.25,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, but we need to run\none more test.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.64,0:05:22.91,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Wha...?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.50,0:05:25.62,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Would you mind going to the\NSensory Deprivation Chamber?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.26,0:05:26.86,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.65,0:05:35.62,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it, what's\nall this about?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.15,0:05:40.70,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"Sensory Deprivation Chamber" sounds a bit\nominous, but there's nothing to be afraid of.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.29,0:05:44.40,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's simply an empty room. With one difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.79,0:05:45.84,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We're ready\nto begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.33,0:05:47.63,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,All right, here goes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.93,0:05:49.09,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.21,0:05:58.80,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This whole thing is stupid. What am I, a kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.02,0:06:03.94,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,As if an astronaut would be scared\nof something like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.76,0:06:07.64,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, this takes me back!\NI did this during training!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.39,0:06:10.07,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't take it for more\nthan 15 minutes at first.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.59,0:06:14.11,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,When I heard that you have to stay in\nfor 6 hours to get your EVA license,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.43,0:06:15.89,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...I nearly passed out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.09,0:06:17.32,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Heart rate climbing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.20,0:06:19.17,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But it's only been\ntwo minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.70,0:06:22.52,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Perspiration increasing.\NBlood pressure climbing, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.23,0:06:23.88,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I thought as much.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.87,0:06:28.79,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,When I read the incident report,\NI thought this might be the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.30,0:06:31.95,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's a condition that rarely\nturns up in EVA workers.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.73,0:06:36.01,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He was floating alone in space,\ncut off from all communication, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.58,0:06:39.36,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The terror he felt then has been\nburned into his body.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.25,0:06:42.72,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Spatial Loss Disorder.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.45,0:06:48.20,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Increase in blood pressure, rapid breathing,\npanic, disorientation...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.69,0:06:50.69,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,There are sometimes even intense\nvisual and auditory hallucinations.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.70,0:06:55.02,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If left untreated, it's a fatal blow\nto an astronaut's career.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.14,0:07:04.43,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That guy is full of crap! What a quack!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.50,0:07:11.53,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It was right after work, so I was tired\nthat day! I hadn't eaten anything, either!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.02,0:07:13.67,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They'll slap a name on anything\nand call it a disease!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.80,0:07:15.51,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hachimaki, you're spitting\nyour food...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.83,0:07:17.58,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, I'm ready for 'em\nthis time!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.93,0:07:19.94,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'll stay in that room until I'm\nnearly dead from starvation!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.20,0:07:21.20,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Just you watch,\nyou quack!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.18,0:07:25.74,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Right! I'll be back later.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.08,0:07:30.81,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think Senpai's\ngonna be okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.68,0:07:35.21,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, it's a psychological problem.\NWhether or not he recovers is up to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.54,0:07:39.24,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Well, with his spirit, I think he'll be fine.\NHe's an optimist.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.71,0:07:43.07,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I guess you're right.\NHe's not that fragile a person.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.41,0:07:46.57,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No, Hachimaki is an EVA specialist.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.15,0:07:49.91,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If this turns out to be Spatial Loss Disorder,\nhis license will be revoked.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.69,0:07:51.38,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Revoked?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.12,0:07:55.00,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He'll never be able to go out\ninto space again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.72,0:07:58.01,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He has to be terrified\nof that possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.34,0:08:07.38,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What the...?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.85,0:08:10.32,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,M-My ears!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.18,0:08:15.14,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The sound... It's inside... my head!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.92,0:08:19.43,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,T-The wall! Where's the wall?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.43,0:08:21.35,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Son of a...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.11,0:08:37.51,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Get Sea of Tranquility General\NHospital on the phone!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.98,0:08:38.57,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.48,0:08:46.24,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it... Spatial Loss Disorder.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.84,0:08:57.32,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So, is Hoshino's rehabilitation\ncoming along smoothly?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.82,0:09:01.09,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He's receiving medication and\nmental training on the moon, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.87,0:09:03.10,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not optimistic\nabout his chances.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.72,0:09:04.92,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,After all,\nit's all in his head.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.87,0:09:06.40,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.68,0:09:07.61,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Are you worried\nabout him?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.17,0:09:10.64,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just... We're colleagues.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.05,0:09:15.34,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How did it go, Lavie-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.21,0:09:18.76,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The other departments should be able\nto juggle their schedules to cover for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.23,0:09:22.10,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Should we go ahead and send\NFee-san and Yu-chan to the moon, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.36,0:09:23.22,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose so.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.76,0:09:27.26,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We can't take a break\nlike everyone else, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.84,0:09:47.58,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yuri-san, you're going\nto the moon, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.91,0:09:48.28,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.21,0:09:52.21,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hachimaki's reinstatement\ntest is this weekend.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.81,0:09:55.17,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to trouble you, but could you\ngive this to Hachimaki?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.99,0:09:59.71,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's a care package. We all pitched in.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.49,0:10:04.38,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He probably doesn't want to see anybody,\nbut could you give this to him for us?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.16,0:10:06.70,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.68,0:10:13.72,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He is, huh? I had heard about it from Hakim,\nbut this sounds bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.00,0:10:16.02,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Tanabe's staying\nwith him now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.30,0:10:20.47,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Spatial Loss Disorder is a psychological\nsickness. He might have trouble getting over it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.78,0:10:23.85,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I know. Depending on the test results,\nhe might be sent back to Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.67,0:10:27.04,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hachi won't be happy about it,\nbut there's no other way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.20,0:10:31.58,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm no doctor, but I know something\nthat might do the trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.97,0:10:34.46,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We'll give it a shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.05,0:10:38.62,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If he's a real astronaut, it should work\nbetter than any stupid rehabilitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.19,0:10:41.66,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But if it doesn't, I won't\nhave any other choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.57,0:10:44.35,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'll give him his dismissal\npapers myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.43,0:10:46.30,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'll have him...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.75,0:10:50.69,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'll have Hachimaki\ngo back down to Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.56,0:11:00.36,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I ran into the ninjas\nbefore I came here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.91,0:11:02.05,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They say they have\njobs now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.71,0:11:05.25,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,At that test site on the\ndark side of the moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.65,0:11:08.17,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You know, where they're building\nthe Von Braun's engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.55,0:11:08.93,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.92,0:11:18.07,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hoshino Hachirota-san of room 204,\npreparations for your testing are now complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.07,0:11:20.03,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Please report to the Sensory Deprivation Chamber.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.83,0:11:23.50,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hoshino Hachirota-san of room 2004...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.02,0:11:24.84,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Senpai...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.30,0:11:28.92,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I've been in rehab for two weeks.\NI'll be fine this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.00,0:11:32.85,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah... I'll be okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.34,0:11:42.15,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hachimaki? Is it time\nfor your test?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.59,0:11:44.04,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh... Uh... Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.76,0:11:48.07,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,See you later. The doctor's waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.39,0:11:52.15,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, Nono-chan. We can talk\nafter the test is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.35,0:11:54.45,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sure. Tests are important.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.36,0:11:58.32,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Let's begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.34,0:11:59.80,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.18,0:12:06.09,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I've taken my medicine.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.83,0:12:07.70,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I've been through rehab.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.55,0:12:09.48,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm rested up, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.29,0:12:13.34,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I can't possibly fail\na simple test like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.55,0:12:21.10,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The sea? Where am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.79,0:12:33.43,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.31,0:12:35.75,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Then, this is...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.65,0:12:45.22,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.82,0:12:47.64,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What is all this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.70,0:12:54.23,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right... I'm a...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.33,0:12:59.94,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Now I remember...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.65,0:13:03.81,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm an astronaut. A debris hauler.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.60,0:13:05.97,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Who's there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.10,0:13:11.63,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You felt it, didn't you? While you were\ndrifting in that radiation storm.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.25,0:13:12.87,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Say what?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.42,0:13:15.01,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"I might die out here."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.89,0:13:17.66,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But that thought actually came as a relief.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.25,0:13:19.08,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What're you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.83,0:13:22.71,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If a man puts his mind to it, he can get married\nor even buy a spaceship!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.63,0:13:26.62,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, is that him? The idiot who says\nhe's gonna buy his own ship?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.79,0:13:28.55,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Did you buy your\nspaceship yet, mister?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.80,0:13:31.53,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you said you were gonna work\nhard until you had your own spaceship!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.53,0:13:33.31,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't getting a spaceship\nyour dream, Senpai?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.20,0:13:35.22,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You know, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.83,0:13:41.03,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You know a lowly junk jockey like you\nwill never get his own spaceship.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.34,0:13:43.76,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me what I can't do!\NI'll get one, no matter what!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.96,0:13:46.31,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I understand... It's all clear now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.06,0:13:52.93,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A lowly debris collector could work for decades\nand still not be able to buy a real spaceship.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.28,0:13:57.23,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Is me buying a spaceship\nthat funny?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.23,0:13:59.44,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it, I haven't even gotten\nmy spaceship yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.09,0:14:02.94,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The reason you kept spouting\nthat crap was because...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.35,0:14:05.81,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...you wanted to stay in\nyour little dream world.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.73,0:14:07.03,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.40,0:14:09.02,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Screw you! I still haven't...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.83,0:14:11.93,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Having dreams that are too big\nwill ruin a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.60,0:14:14.84,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Even you have to realize that. Even you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.58,0:14:20.90,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. You've seen it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.84,0:14:25.65,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You've seen how it always ends.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.99,0:14:32.91,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You've heard the expression\N"know your limitations," haven't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.73,0:14:36.78,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They're finally letting me\ncarry people now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.70,0:14:40.61,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Let it go. Any more of this, and you'll make us\nthink that you have an inferiority complex.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.76,0:14:44.16,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, you talk the talk, but you settled down\nand got complacent the first chance you got!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.42,0:14:51.30,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You can't fight your way though, so now you're\nfinally starting to look for an excuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.74,0:14:52.56,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,An excuse?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.18,0:14:53.70,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.55,0:14:55.13,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.88,0:14:56.46,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.04,0:14:59.68,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This sickness of yours\nis exactly what you wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.52,0:15:00.94,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.11,0:15:08.10,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Families? Why are you\nshowing me this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.39,0:15:08.93,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'll leave them love!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.46,0:15:09.84,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Tanabe?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.74,0:15:13.27,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Living alone\nand dying alone...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.17,0:15:14.82,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Alone...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.76,0:15:17.47,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How could anyone\nbe satisfied with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.33,0:15:18.97,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.44,0:15:21.46,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,She's cute, isn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.72,0:15:23.41,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's not so bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.18,0:15:27.13,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No, it doesn't sound so bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.25,0:15:31.61,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Go down to Earth, get married,\ngrow old...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.89,0:15:32.84,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.68,0:15:43.44,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You wanted the right to look up at the\nlights in the night sky and say,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.21,0:15:46.24,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,..."If it wasn't for that sickness,\NI'd still be up there right now."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.71,0:15:51.10,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"I didn't give up or anything. It's not my fault."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.42,0:15:52.77,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"It was because\nof that accident."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.57,0:15:56.28,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"If it wasn't for that accident, I know I'd..."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.77,0:15:59.03,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Give me a\nstraight answer!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.90,0:16:07.75,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Is it just me, or does\nhe eat more than Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.25,0:16:10.76,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's for the best.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.76,0:16:12.21,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Like hell! Shut the hell up!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.61,0:16:15.38,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Admit it. Accept reality.\NMake it easy for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.68,0:16:16.58,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Apologize for lying\nto yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.76,0:16:18.05,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up! Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.66,0:16:22.18,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Space might not love you,\nbut it will forgive you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.73,0:16:23.64,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Shut the hell up!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.78,0:16:31.43,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Senpai!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.93,0:16:32.71,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Get a medical team\nin here!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.63,0:16:35.44,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A stretcher! Go get a stretcher!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.24,0:16:53.70,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You sure get depressed easily,\nyou know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.37,0:16:56.05,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And after all those speeches\nyou've given to me...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.64,0:17:00.34,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Still, you're able to stay\nin there longer now, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.74,0:17:03.83,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The rehab must be working.\NYou were in there a whole 20 minutes today.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.91,0:17:09.10,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I got a message from Fee-san and Yuri-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.02,0:17:12.94,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They're in Tranquility City right now,\nso they should be here pretty soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.13,0:17:19.31,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Senpai... Maybe it would be better\nif you went back to Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.98,0:17:25.86,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You could breathe fresh air\nand tackle this nice and slowly.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.92,0:17:29.80,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Let me handle the Fishbone\nwhile you're away.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.04,0:17:33.35,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm pretty good\nat the job now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.37,0:17:36.95,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay, space isn't\ngoing anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.71,0:17:40.20,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,There's always gonna be lots of debris\nthat will need to be brought in.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.60,0:17:42.07,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Senpai?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.98,0:17:44.50,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Senpai!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.58,0:17:48.16,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's right, Hoshino Hachirota.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.91,0:17:50.89,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He's been\nchecked in here since last month.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.71,0:17:53.07,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Tanabe!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.96,0:17:54.42,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yuri-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.16,0:17:57.24,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Good timing. We were just...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.24,0:17:57.92,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's Senpai!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.72,0:18:00.52,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He's missing!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.91,0:18:06.98,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This is a page for Hoshino-san\nof room 204.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.39,0:18:08.60,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hoshino Hachirota-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.41,0:18:14.20,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hoshino Hachirota-san of room 204,\N please come to the reception desk at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.65,0:18:19.21,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Nono-chan! Have you\nseen Hachimaki?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.41,0:18:20.91,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No, sorry. Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.33,0:18:22.19,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He's missing!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.59,0:18:27.03,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He hasn't gone through the gate,\nso I think he's still in the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.23,0:18:30.03,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What is it? Do you know where he is?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.73,0:18:33.58,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe... Maybe he's over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.67,0:18:46.40,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You gotta be kidding me!\NI'll never get better on Earth!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.33,0:18:54.01,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Senpai...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.84,0:18:55.85,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.42,0:18:59.00,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I wanna stay\nin space...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.06,0:19:04.55,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No way am I gonna let everything\NI've worked for go down the tubes...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.16,0:19:05.91,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I won't!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.64,0:19:08.75,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Senpai, stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.42,0:19:13.18,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.96,0:19:15.96,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'll never go into\nspace again...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.70,0:19:19.48,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This is suicide.\NOr is this some kind of special training?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.76,0:19:20.49,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Screw you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.88,0:19:24.42,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I seem to recall an astronaut who died\nout here on the surface of the moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.71,0:19:28.28,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Well, maybe that's better than living\nwith a lifetime of regret.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.75,0:19:31.92,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Still, you aren't in such\na hurry to die...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.95,0:19:34.72,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...that you can't put up with a little meddling\nfrom your teammates, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.15,0:19:48.09,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It took a lot of doing to\nget these visitor's permits.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.47,0:19:51.90,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Gigalt-san said this might be just\nwhat the doctor ordered.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.29,0:19:52.91,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He said that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.44,0:20:04.64,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Glad you could\nmake it, Hoshino.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.69,0:20:06.37,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hakim?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.80,0:20:09.03,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks. I guess we're making\na lot of trouble for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.33,0:20:12.25,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don't mention it. We're both students\nof the Gigalt School.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.66,0:20:20.13,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Feast your eyes on this, Hachi.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.80,0:20:23.45,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A little something to take\nwith you to the afterlife.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.51,0:20:28.64,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The tandem mirror\nnuclear fusion engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.03,0:20:30.92,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The most powerful engine\never built.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.89,0:20:35.91,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It uses the deuterium-helium 3\nfusion reaction to generate thrust.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.68,0:20:39.67,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,High-speed, charged particles\nare generated inside\Nthe fusion chamber at 500 million\ndegrees Celsius.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.34,0:20:41.62,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They are controlled by means\nof magnetic fields,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.12,0:20:44.76,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...and released along with propellant\nfrom its nozzle in back.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.65,0:20:47.08,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It has a specific impulse\nof 600,000 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.75,0:20:49.55,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's about 10,000 times greater than our own ship's.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.63,0:20:57.89,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This is the main engine that will be mounted\nin the Jupiter explorer, the Von Braun.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.59,0:21:03.21,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If we can use this to develop the Jovian system,\nit will make a great fuel supply center.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.77,0:21:09.74,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Before too long, astronauts are\ngoing to have their hands full.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.46,0:21:15.71,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The solar system\nis going to change.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.50,0:21:18.67,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,At times like this,\nthe world needs fools.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.43,0:21:21.93,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It needs people\nlike you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.61,0:21:42.44,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You seem relaxed today.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.24,0:21:46.72,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Let me ask you something.\NWhat have you decided?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.89,0:21:51.16,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Nah, I'm not really any\ndifferent from before.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.17,0:21:54.45,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No, I take that back. Maybe I have changed a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.47,0:21:56.54,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Something occurred\nto me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.36,0:22:02.67,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe the engineers who built that engine\nalso had to fight things like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.81,0:22:08.44,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,There in the darkness, blind, groping along\nand trying to find their way,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.38,0:22:12.39,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...I bet they all went through\nthat same experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.42,0:22:18.16,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Even Tsiolkovsky. And Goddard.\NAnd Oberth. And Von Braun.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.28,0:22:24.51,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But once I swore to myself that\NI'd fight you my whole life,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.66,0:22:27.92,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...I knew I'd see\nthe light eventually.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.77,0:22:33.13,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go for now. But don't let\nyour guard down, Hachimaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.25,0:22:39.90,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I might come back when\nyou least expect me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.01,0:22:41.91,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Test cleared.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.07,0:22:43.77,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Senpai!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.21,0:22:45.92,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Senpai!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.49,0:22:57.36,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.37,0:23:00.32,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be ready for you.
